label.value: Maturing Erythroid Cell to Total Cell Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of maturing erythroid cells compared to total cells present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: Maturing Myeloid Cell to Total Cell Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of maturing myeloid cells compared to total cells present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.
Any one of the air-filled spaces within the ethmoid, frontal, maxillary, or sphenoid bones, which communicate with the nasal cavity.
The determination of the amount of murinoglobulin present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of para-aminohippurate sodium present in a sample.

label.value: Proliferating Erythroid Cell to Total Cell Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of proliferating erythroid cells compared to total cells present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.
The determination of the amount of plasminogen present in a sample.

label.value: Proliferating Myeloid Cell to Total Cell Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of proliferating myeloid cells compared to total cells present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.
The determination of the amount of S100 calcium-binding protein B present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of toponin I type 2 present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of WD-repeat containing protein 26 present in a sample.

label.value: Left Coronary Cusp of the Aortic Valve

value.value: The cusp of the aortic valve that overlies the left coronary ostium.

label.value: Non-Coronary Cusp of the Aortic Valve

value.value: The cusp of the aortic valve that is positioned posteriorly relative to the other two aortic cusps.

The division of the autonomic nervous system responsible for conserving and restoring energy (opposing the sympathetic nervous system), which arises from preganglionic cell bodies in the gray matter of the brain stem and the middle three segments of the sacral cord.

label.value: Right Coronary Cusp of the Aortic Valve

The terminus of the aortic root; the point at which the aorta attains a tubular configuration.

The funnel-shaped structure through which blood flows from the left ventricle into the aortic root.

The lateral segment of the right ventricular wall, excluding the anterior and inferior right ventricular wall.
The funnel-shaped structure through which blood flows from the right ventricle into the pulmonary trunk.
The wall of the right ventricle, comprising anterior, inferior, and lateral walls; and excluding the interventricular septum.

One of two small paired endocrine glands, superior and inferior, usually found embedded in the connective tissue capsule on the posterior surface of the thyroid gland; these glands secrete parathyroid hormone that regulates the metabolism of calcium and phosphorus. label.value: Anterior Annulus of the Mitral Valve

value.value: The portion of the mitral valve annulus that attaches to the anterior mitral valve leaflet, and also forms the mitral portion of the aortic-mitral curtain.

label.value: Anterior Cusp of the Mitral Valve

value.value: The cusp of the mitral valve that is anchored to the aortic-mitral curtain.
The bony, basin-shaped structure formed by the hipbones and the base of the backbone supporting the lower limbs in humans.

label.value: Posterior Annulus of the Mitral Valve

value.value: The portion of the mitral valve annulus that attaches to the posterior mitral valve leaflet.

label.value: Posterior Cusp of the Mitral Valve

value.value: The cusp of the mitral valave that is located posterior to the two commissures, and which has no attachement to the aortic root.
The wall of the pericardium, comprising the following tissue layers: the fibrous pericardium; the parietal and visceral layers of the serous pericardium.
